# Appendix exercise A-2: cubic fields with prescribed discriminant

Exercise A-2(a) constructs a non-Galois cubic field of discriminant `-d` or
`-4d` from a Hilbert or ray class field of `Q(sqrt(-d))`.  Its proof needs the
existence theorem of global class field theory together with detailed
ramification-to-discriminant calculations for cubic subfields.  Those
interfaces are not yet present in Mathlib or `Towers.NumberTheory.Milne`.

Part (b) explicitly asks for a computation of the smallest cubic discriminant.
It is intentionally omitted under the project's computation-heavy exception.
-/
